  "title": "react-instantsearch-nextjs breaks on Cloudflare Pages",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nThe NextJS package with routing has hanging promises which fail and break the SSR renderer in the worker on Cloudflare Pages. My guess is it's a fetch implementation that's broken in their environment. \n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create an app router page in Nextjs 14. \r\n2. Install the nextjs instantsearch package and render it\r\n3. Deploy to cloudflare pages\r\n4. Cloudflare pages will throw an error: `[Uncaught (in response) Error: The script will never generate a response]`\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nhttps://codesandbox.io/p/sandbox/solitary-grass-lqknn5?workspaceId=ws_CUwuwFRhcyzgdBykwr8y6o\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\nThe worker is able to return a proper error message or actually just render the page.\n\n### Package version\n\nreact-instantsearch-nextjs 0.3.20\n\n### Operating system\n\n_No response_\n\n### Browser\n\n_No response_\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [X] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
